<sect1 id="_CONSTANT">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>#CONSTANT</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para><emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->CONSTANT<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary>#<!-- DNT-Start -->CONSTANT<!-- DNT-End --></primary>
    </indexterm>( </emphasis><emphasis>name, value </emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">);</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="75.05pt" />

        <colspec colwidth="277.75pt" />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>name</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>A string constant containing the name of the stored
            value.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>value</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>An expression for the value to assign to the stored
            name.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->CONSTANT<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>statement is similar to
  #<!-- DNT-Start -->STORED<!-- DNT-End --> in that it assigns the <emphasis>value</emphasis> to the
  <emphasis>name</emphasis>, but #<!-- DNT-Start -->CONSTANT<!-- DNT-End --> specifies the value is not
  over-writable at runtime. This statement may be used outside an <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> scope
  and does not require a previous <!-- DNT-Start -->LOADXML<!-- DNT-End --> to instantiate an <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> scope.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>  PersonCount := 0 : STORED('myname');
  #CONSTANT('myname',100);
      //make stored PersonCount attribute value to 100
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="_STORED">#<!-- DNT-Start -->STORED<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
